(
  'Hessequa Local Municipality Bursary South Africa 2025',
  'HESSEQUA MUNICIPALITY',
  'Students will be paid a stipend, which must be used for meals, accommodation and transport costs. The bursary will be awarded for 1 year of study. Theoretical training will take place at the institution and the practical work experience will take place in Riversdale. www.zabur...',
  NULL,
  0,
  NULL,
  'https://www.hessequa.gov.za/',
  'https://www.zabursaries.co.za/government-bursaries-south-africa/hessequa-local-municipality-bursary/',
  ARRAY['mailto:jaundre@hessequa.gov.za', 'https://www.hessequa.gov.za/', 'mailto: jaundre@hessequa.gov.za']::text[],
  'Students will be paid a stipend, which must be used for meals, accommodation and transport costs. The bursary will be awarded for 1 year of study. Theoretical training will take place at the institution and the practical work experience will take place in Riversdale. www.zabursaries.co.za is committed to keeping you up to date with the latest bursary opportunities, and this article covers all details about the Hessequa Local Municipality Bursary.',
  'Applicants must satisfy the following minimum entry criteria before applying for the bursary (please note that failure to satisfy all the requirements will lead to your application not being considered): You must be a South African citizen You must reside within the Hessequa Municipal area, in the Western Cape province You must be between 18 and 23 years old You must have completed Matric You must be studying or intend on studying towards one of the qualifications listed above You must be registered to study at an accredited tertiary institution in South Africa You must have a strong academic record You must NOT be receiving another bursary award or NSFAS funding You must have a desire to uplift and change the community for the better You must be in financial need (unable to afford to study towards a degree) Students with disabilities and students from historically disadvantaged groups are encouraged to apply',
  'Download and complete the Hessequa Municipality Bursary Application Form 2025 (.pdf) Enter “www.zabursaries.co.za” in the field asking how you heard about the Hessequa Municipality bursary. Submit clear copies of the following supporting documentation along with your completed application form (the submission of these documents is compulsory – if any items are missing, your application be disqualified): ID document (certified copy: not older than 3 months) Matric certificate Proof of qualification/ latest examination results Proof of tertiary registration (on institution''s letterhead) Proof of residential address (recent municipal account) Parents or guardians proof of income (latest payslips if employed: certified copy, affidavit if unemployed etc) Comprehensive Curriculum Vitae Proof of disability, if applicable (letter from a medical doctor confirming permanent disability) Applications must be submitted via email to: jaundre@hessequa.gov.za (Insert the words “ Hessequa Municipality Bursary 2025 ” in the email subject line).',
  'Accounting',
  ARRAY['All']::text[],
  ARRAY['Accounting', 'Civil Engineering', 'Economics', 'Electrical Engineering', 'Finance', 'Information Communication Technology (ICT)', 'Infrastructure', 'Internal Audit', 'Risk Management', 'Supply Chain Management', 'The bursary will be awarded for 1 year of study.']::text[],
  FALSE,
  TRUE,
  now()
),
(
  'iSimangaliso Wetland Park Bursary South Africa 2026',
  'ISIMANGALISO',
  'Applicants must satisfy the following minimum entry criteria before applying (please note that failure to satisfy all the requirements will lead to your application not being considered): You must be a South African citizen You must be a verifiable member of either: The Land C...',
  NULL,
  0,
  '2026-02-15',
  'https://resources.isimangaliso.com/images/files/education/Application%20form_Tertiary%20Edu%20Support%202026.pdf',
  'https://www.zabursaries.co.za/science-bursaries-south-africa/isimangaliso-wetland-park-bursary/',
  ARRAY['mailto:nosipho@isimangaliso.com', 'https://resources.isimangaliso.com/images/files/education/Application%20form_Tertiary%20Edu%20Support%202026.pdf', 'mailto: nosipho@isimangaliso.com']::text[],
  NULL,
  'Applicants must satisfy the following minimum entry criteria before applying (please note that failure to satisfy all the requirements will lead to your application not being considered): You must be a South African citizen You must be a verifiable member of either: The Land Claimants Communities from iSimangaliso Wetland Park Authority (Sokhulu, Bhangazi, Dukuduku, Western Shores, Mdletsheni, Makhasa, Mnqobokazi, Nside, Ngwenya, Jobe, Mabaso, Emandleni, (Mbila) and Triangle (Mbila), and Coastal Reserves); OR be a resident of areas of Mkhanyakude District Municipality that are close to iSimangaliso Wetland Park or the Mfolozi Local Municipality particularly in the Sokhulu area You must intend on studying towards a qualification within the Conservation, Tourism or a related discipline You must entering your 1st year of study in 2026 You must be accepted to study at one the following institutions: University of KwaZulu-Natal, University of Zululand, Mangosuthu University of Technology and Durban University of Technology You must have applied for NSFAS bursary, or have confirmation that you have been awarded a NSFAS bursary You must have a passion for nature',
  'Download and complete the iSimangaliso Wetland Park Bursary Application Form 2026 (.pdf) Enter “www.zabursaries.co.za” in the field asking how you heard about the iSimangaliso Wetland Park Bursary. Submit clear copies of the following supporting documentation along with your completed application form (the submission of these documents is compulsory – if any items are missing, your may application be disqualified): ID document (certified copy) Proof of NSFAS bursary application Proof of registration or acceptance to UKZN, UniZulu, MUT or DUT Proof of residence If you are a member of a land claimant community: official letter from the Chairperson of the Board of Trustees of your land claim Trust confirming that you are a member of the land claim community If you are a member of iSimangaliso neighbouring communities: official letter from your local leader / councillor confirming that you are from the area and the length of time you have been living there Applications must be submitted via email to: nosipho@isimangaliso.com (Insert the words " iSimangaliso Bursary 2026 " in the email subject line).',
  'Accounting; Commerce; Construction & Built Environment; General',
  ARRAY['All']::text[],
  ARRAY[]::text[],
  FALSE,
  TRUE,
  now()
),
(
  'KwaDukuza Municipality Bursary South Africa 2026',
  'KWADUKUZA MUNICIPALITY',
  'The bursary will cover the following expenses: registration or admission fees to the value of R10 000. www.zabursaries.co.za is committed to keeping you up to date with the latest bursary opportunities, and this article covers all details about the KwaDukuza Municipality Bursa...',
  NULL,
  0,
  '2026-01-22',
  'https://www.zabursaries.co.za/government-bursaries-south-africa/kwadukuza-municipality-bursary/',
  'https://www.zabursaries.co.za/government-bursaries-south-africa/kwadukuza-municipality-bursary/',
  ARRAY['https://www.zabursaries.co.za/government-bursaries-south-africa/kwadukuza-municipality-bursary/']::text[],
  'The bursary will cover the following expenses: registration or admission fees to the value of R10 000. www.zabursaries.co.za is committed to keeping you up to date with the latest bursary opportunities, and this article covers all details about the KwaDukuza Municipality Bursary.',
  'Applicants must satisfy the following minimum entry criteria before applying (please note that failure to satisfy all the requirements will lead to your application not being considered): You must reside within KwaDukuza area of jurisdiction, in KwaZulu-Natal province You must have completed Matric You must have achieved University entrance or endorsement in Matric You must be studying or intend on studying full-time, towards an undergraduate National Diploma or Degree, in one of the fields listed above You must be studying or intend on studying at a recognized and accredited public tertiary institution in South Africa You must NOT be in receipt of any other bursary funding or NSFAS funding You must NOT have completed any other qualification or degree or diploma You must have a strong academic record You must be in financial need You must be from a previously disadvantaged background',
  'Download and complete the KwaDukuza Municipality Bursary Application Form 2026 (.pdf) Alternatively, application forms can also be collected from the KwaDukuza Youth Centre, as well as libraries within the jurisdiction of KwaDukuza and other municipal offices. Enter “www.zabursaries.co.za” in the field asking how you heard about the KwaDukuza Municipality bursary. Submit clear copies of the following supporting documentation along with your completed bursary application form (the submission of these documents is compulsory – if any items are missing, your application may be disqualified): ID document (certified copy) New Students: Matric certificate and statement of results (certified copy) Returning students: original progress report, with marks, symbols, percentages for all examinations written (certified copy) Motivational letter stating why you should be awarded the bursary (read our tips on how to write a motivational letter for your bursary application ) Proof of tertiary admission/ acceptance/ conditional or firm offer (on institutions letterhead) Curriculum from institution for selected course of study, stating number of years of study, number of modules/ subjects to be taken (on institutions letterhead) Tuition fees statement from institution (on institutions letterhead) Parents or guardians proof of income (latest payslips if employed, affidavit or letter from the Department of Labour if unemployed) Parents or guardians list of monthly expenses Proof of residents in KwaDukuza Applications must be submitted in one of the following ways: - Post: The Municipal Manager: KwaDukuza Municipality P.O Box 72 KwaDukuza 4450 - Hand delivery: KwaDukuza Municipality Youth Development Office 42 Goolam Suleman Street KwaDukuza 4450 Note: applications must be marked “KwaDukuza External Bursary 2026” and should be in a sealed envelope.',
  'Accounting; Construction & Built Environment',
  ARRAY['All']::text[],
  ARRAY['Evaluation, Housing, Legal, Community and Economic Development studies']::text[],
  FALSE,
  TRUE,
  now()
),
