  NULL,
  'Applicants must satisfy the following minimum entry criteria before applying (please note that failure to satisfy all the requirements will lead to your application not being considered): You must be a South African citizen You must be studying at a recognised and accredited tertiary institution in South Africa You must be studying on a full-time basis Civil Engineering, Industrial Engineering, Metallurgical/ Chemical Engineering students: you must be entering your 2nd or 4th year of study Electrical Engineering, Mechanical Engineering, Mining Engineering students: you must be entering your 2nd year of study Geology students: you must be entering your 2nd or 3rd year of study Data Science: you must be entering your 3rd year of study Mine Surveying students: you must be entering your 3rd or Honours year of study You must be able to achieve and maintain the required minimum academic average as indicated in the bursary agreement You must be committed to completing all studies, assignments, projects, and examinations You must be willing to submit academic transcripts or progress updates each semester/term to the bursary office You must be willing to participate in bursary-related programs, including mentoring, workshops, or community outreach initiatives You must be willing complete any service obligations or internships after graduation You must be ambitious and hard working You must be passionate about engineering',
  'Applications must be submitted online at: Exxaro Bursary Application 2026 (Reference number: EXX251104-3) Enter “www.zabursaries.co.za” in the field asking how you heard about the Exxaro bursary. Submit clear copies of the following supporting documentation along with your online application (the submission of these documents is compulsory - if any items are missing, your application may be disqualified): ID document (certified copy) Matric certificate (certified copy) Full tertiary record/ transcripts (on institutions letterhead) Curriculum Vitae',
