  NULL,
  'Applicants must satisfy the following minimum entry criteria before applying (please note that failure to satisfy all the requirements will lead to your application not being considered): You must be a South African citizen You must be under 35 years old You must have completed Matric or equivalent You must be studying full-time towards one of the qualifications listed above You must be studying at a recognised and accredited tertiary institution in South Africa You must have achieved a minimum overall average of 65% and academic performance in major subject You must be interested in working within the water sector You must be from a previously disadvantaged background You must NOT be receiving any other bursary awards or funding You must be self-motivated You must be results-driven You must have good written and verbal communication skills You must intend on completing your qualification within the specified amount of time, per the bursary agreement Preference will be given to female students, as well as students with disabilities (in line with Rand Water''s Employment Equity objectives)',
  'Applications must be submitted online at: Rand Water Bursary Application 2025 (Reference number: RAN250123-2) Applicants will be required to Register an Account before they can Login and apply. Enter “www.zabursaries.co.za” in the field asking how you heard about the Rand Water Bursary. Submit clear copies of the following supporting documentation along with your application (the submission of these documents is compulsory – if any items are missing, your application may be disqualified): ID document (certified copy) Matric certificate (certified copy) Most recent academic record (on institutions letterhead) Proof of Registration/ Acceptance letter (on institutions letterhead)',
  'General',
  ARRAY['All']::text[],
  ARRAY['Accounting / Finance: B Comm (1 bursary to be awarded, to a 3rd year student)', 'Chemistry: BSc (2 bursaries to be awarded, to 2nd year students)', 'Corporate Communication: B Comm (1 bursary to be awarded, to a 2nd year student)', 'Economics: BCom (2 bursaries to be awarded, to 2nd and 3rd year students)', 'Electrical: Diploma (2 bursaries to be awarded, to 2nd year students)', 'Hydrology / Modeling: BSc Hons (1 bursary to be awarded, to a 4th year student)', 'Maintenance Engineering: BEng (3 bursaries to be awarded, to 2nd year students)', 'Mechanical Engineering: BEng (3 bursaries to be awarded, to 2nd year students)', 'Microbiology: BSc Hons (1 bursary to be awarded, to a 2nd year student)']::text[],
  FALSE,
  TRUE,
  now()
),
